# Stack Constraints

## Approved stack — use these, nothing else

### Frontend
| Concern | Approved | Forbidden alternatives |
|---------|----------|----------------------|
| Framework | Next.js 14 App Router | CRA, Vite+React, Remix |
| Server state | TanStack Query | SWR, React Query v3, Apollo Client |
| Forms | React Hook Form + zod | Formik, react-final-form, Yup alone |
| UI components | shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) | MUI, Ant Design, Chakra UI |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | styled-components, emotion, CSS modules |
| Global state | React context + useState | Redux, Zustand, Jotai, MobX |

### Backend
| Concern | Approved | Forbidden alternatives |
|---------|----------|----------------------|
| Framework | NestJS | Express alone, Fastify, Hono |
| ORM | Prisma | TypeORM, Sequelize, Drizzle, knex |
| Validation | class-validator + class-transformer | joi, zod on backend, manual validation |
| HTTP docs | @nestjs/swagger | swagger-jsdoc, manual OpenAPI |
| Error tracking | @sentry/node | Bugsnag, Rollbar, custom solutions |

### Infrastructure
| Concern | Approved |
|---------|----------|
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |
| Container | Docker Compose |
| Metrics | Prometheus + prom-client |
| Logs | Structured JSON → Loki via Promtail |

## Hard rules

```ts
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — never add these imports
import { createStore } from 'redux';
import create from 'zustand';
import useSWR from 'swr';
import { useQuery } from '@apollo/client';
import { styled } from 'styled-components';
import { Form } from 'formik';

// ✅ APPROVED equivalents
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';   // shadcn
```

## Adding a new dependency
Before adding any package not in the approved list:
1. Check if an approved library already covers the use case
2. If genuinely missing, document the reason in the PR description
3. Never add a dependency just because it's familiar from another project
